With `Mutex<Option<StateRecorder>>`, this becomes:
```rust
pub fn record(event_type: EventType, actor: Actor, payload: Value) {
    let guard = GLOBAL_RECORDER.lock().unwrap_or_else(|e| e.into_inner());
    let Some(recorder) = guard.as_ref() else {
        return;
    };
    if let Err(e) = recorder.append(event_type, actor, payload) {
        if recorder.fail_soft {
            eprintln!("warning: failed to record state event: {e}");
        } else {
            panic!("failed to record state event: {e}");
        }
    }
}
```

This is clean. The lock is held while `append` runs, which is fast (file write). The guard is dropped after the if-let.

