Now I understand the root cause. `GLOBAL_RECORDER` is a `OnceLock<StateRecorder>` — it can only be set once per process lifetime. The first test that calls `init_global` sets it, and subsequent tests can't replace it. Their `init_global` silently fails to set the global, so the guard's `record()` calls go to the old (deleted) tempdir's recorder.

Fix: change `OnceLock<StateRecorder>` to `Mutex<Option<StateRecorder>>`, which allows tests to reset the global.
